sevenz-rs — memory-safe Rust port of the 7-Zip / LZMA SDK algorithms.

This crate is a derivative work of the C reference implementations
shipped in the 7-Zip source distribution by Igor Pavlov. The upstream
licensing is, per `7-Zip/License.txt`:

  - GNU LGPL (version 2.1 or later) for most of the 7-Zip codebase.
  - BSD 2-Clause / BSD 3-Clause for some files.
  - Public domain for files that originate in the LZMA SDK only
    (the LZMA encoder/decoder, the BCJ family, the SHA / CRC tables,
    the PPMd codecs).

We mirror that structure:

  - Files in this crate that are direct ports of LZMA-SDK code are
    public domain.
  - All other Rust files (the crate-level glue, tests, binaries,
    cross-check harnesses) are licensed under the GNU LGPL, version
    2.1 or, at your option, any later version.

When in doubt, treat the crate as LGPL-2.1+.

